            <lg type="song"><label > Song </label>
               <lg>
                  <l>Hum corpo sem a metade</l>
                  <l>Que possa vivir n&#xE3;o sei</l>
                  <l>Se tu es minha metade</l>
                  <l>Como sem ti vivirei</l>
               </lg></lg>
            <note type="translation"><lg>
               <l>A body without a half</l>
               <l>How I can live I don't know</l>
               <l>If you are my [other] half</l>
               <l>How will I live without you?</l>
            </lg></note>
            <cb/>
            <label type="song"> Song Modinha <note type="editorial">Modinha: a kind of sentimental
               love song popuar in <date notBefore="1701" notAfter="1900">18th- and 19th-century</date> Portugal. 'Modinha', the diminutive of
               'fashion', apparently refers to fashionable aristocratic salons.</note></label>
            <lg>
               <l>Amar para ser amada</l>
               <l>He doce consolac&#xE3;o</l>
               <l>Eu gozo toda esta dita</l>
               <l>Que mais quer o meu corac&#xE3;o.</l>
               <l>Que quer oh que quer</l>
               <l>Gemir suspirar</l>
               <l>Tremer palpitar</l>
               <l>Que quer o meu Corac&#xE3;o.</l>
            </lg>
            <label>2</label>
            <lg>
               <l>Imperios ricos thesauros</l>
               <l>N&#xE3;o me moven ambici&#xE3;o</l>
               <l>Sei que amo e sou amado</l>
               <l>Que mais quer o meu corac&#xE3;o</l>
            </lg>
            <label>3</label>
            <lg>
               <l>Se a minha alma dâ€™outra alma</l>
               <l>Goza a fina adorac&#xE3;o</l>
               <l>Se a vida toda he praze</l>
               <l>Que mais quer o meu corac&#xE3;o.</l>
            </lg>
            <note type="translation">
               <lg>
                  <l>Loving in order to be loved</l>
                  <l>Is sweet consolation.</l>
                  <l>I enjoy the whole saying.</l>
                  <l>What more does my heart want?</l>
                  <l>What does it want? Oh, what does it want?</l>
                  <l>To moan, to sigh,</l>
                  <l>To tremble, to throb.</l>
                  <l>What does my heart want?</l>
               </lg>
               <label>2</label>
               <lg>
                  <l>Empires, riches, treasures</l>
                  <l>Don't move my ambition</l>
                  <l>I know I love and am loved</l>
                  <l>What more does my heart want?</l>
               </lg><label>3</label>
               <lg>
                  <l>If my soul enjoys fine adoration</l>
                  <l>From another soul</l>
                  <l>If all life is pleasurable</l>
                  <l>What more does my heart want?</l>
               </lg></note>
